Key Match Events: Nick Nastrini walked six batters, needing 72 pitches to record five outs
In the second inning, Nastrini threw four pitches to the backstop — two of them in the dirt and two over catcher Korey Lee’s head
A collision in left field cost the White Sox three runs
Post-Match Reflections: The White Sox lost to the Orioles 9-0, their 109th loss of the season
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was decided early and in reckless, uncontrolled fashion
The White Sox were shut out for the 16th time
